SIMPLE: insensate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insensate
<hw>In*sen"sate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>insensatus</ets>. See <er>In-</er> not, and
<er>Sensate</er>.]</ety> <def>Wanting sensibility; destitute of sense;
stupid; foolish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The silence and the calm⟦br⟧
Of mute, <qex>insensate</qex> things.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The meddling folly or <qex>insensate</qex> ambition of
statesmen.</q> <rj><qau>Buckle.</qau></rj></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>In*sen"sate*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>In*sen"sate*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insense</ent>⟦br⟧
